The paper deals with graph separators and hypergraph support, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the structural properties of graphs and hypergraphs, rather than their algorithmic aspects, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely sub-categories.
